Chapter 5: CSS Text Properties

2.2 text-decoration-style property:

the text-decoration-style property defines the different types of styles for the decorative line in the text.

Note: to use this property in the text, we must define any line and color (which is optional) for the text, means we must use the text-decoration-line property and text-decoration-color property which is optional.

5 Values of text-decoration-style property:

solid - display a solid straight line
double - display 2 lines
dotted - display dotted lines
dashed - display dashed lines
wavy - display wavy lines

